page_title: Quickstart - getting started with Azure OpenAI assistants (preview) in AI Studio
page_description: Walkthrough on how to get started with Azure OpenAI assistants with new features like code interpreter in AI Studio (Preview).
chunk_content: Key conceptsWhile using the Assistants playground, keep the following concepts in mind. ### ToolsAn individual assistant can access up to 128 tools including `code interpreter`, as well as any custom tools you create via functions.### Chat sessionChat session also known as a *thread* within the Assistant's API is where the conversation between the user and assistant occurs. Unlike traditional chat completion calls there is no limit to the number of messages in a thread. The assistant will automatically compress requests to fit the input token limit of the model.This also means that you are not controlling how many tokens are passed to the model during each turn of the conversation. Managing tokens is abstracted away and handled entirely by the Assistants API.Select the Clear chat button to delete the current conversation history.Underneath the text input box there are two buttons:- Add a message without run.- Add and run.### LogsLogs provide a detailed snapshot of what the assistant API activity.### Show panelsBy default there are three panels: assistant setup, chat session, and Logs. Show panels allows you to add, remove, and rearrange the panels. If you ever close a panel and need to get it back, use Show panels to restore the lost panel.
